sequenceDiagram
    autonumber
    actor U as User
    participant SF as Salesforce (server)
    participant API as Jetstream Server
    participant DB as PostgreSQL
    participant IF as Browser (Canvas iframe)

    Note over U,IF: User opens Jetstream from inside Salesforce (managed package / Canvas app)

    U->>SF: Open Jetstream (App Launcher / tab)

    rect rgb(230, 244, 234)
    Note over SF,DB: Salesforce authenticates the user and posts a SIGNED REQUEST
    SF->>API: POST /canvas/app  (signed_request = signature.envelope)
    API->>API: verifySignature: HMAC-SHA256(envelope, SFDC_CANVAS_CLIENT_SECRET), timing-safe
    Note over API: Envelope carries oauthToken, instanceUrl,<br/>user + org context. Token is NOT persisted.
    API->>DB: isCanvasOrgEntitled(orgId, instanceUrl)?
    alt Not entitled
        API-->>IF: 403 branded "access denied" page
    end
    end

    rect rgb(232, 240, 254)
    Note over API,IF: Serve the app (assets from Jetstream, Canvas SDK from Salesforce)
    API-->>IF: index.html + React bundle (window.sr = verified envelope)
    IF->>SF: Load Canvas SDK: {instanceUrl}/canvas/sdk/js/.../canvas-all.js
    end

    IF->>IF: Sfdc.canvas.oauth.token(sr.client.oauthToken)
    Note over IF,SF: Authenticated. Salesforce data access goes browser -> Salesforce<br/>via the Canvas SDK (see SF data flow) - never through Jetstream.
